{"componentChunkName":"component---src-templates-post-js","path":"/post/introducing-the-vanilla-template-to-codesandbox","webpackCompilationHash":"43a07f76784e304bf1a0","result":{"data":{"blogPost":{"fields":{"authors":["Ives van Hoorne"],"date":"2018-02-28T00:00:00.000Z","description":"CodeSandbox got support for the Vanilla template, based on the Parcel bundler.","photo":"https://avatars0.githubusercontent.com/u/587016?s=460&v=4","slug":"introducing-the-vanilla-template-to-codesandbox","title":"Introducing the Vanilla Template to CodeSandbox"},"frontmatter":{"banner":{"publicURL":"/static/banner-04b02e3c8bd760bf8004da8941ce5116.png"}},"html":"<p>From day one <a href=\"https://codesandbox.io\">we</a>'ve always tied templates to a CLI. The\nmain reason for this is that we want to keep sandboxes simple, you shouldn't\nneed to do any configuration to get started. I didn't want to create a\n'<code class=\"language-text\">Vanilla</code>' template because there was no way to create 'vanilla' web projects\nwithout configuration, until recently.</p>\n<section>\n<h2 id=\"parcel\"><a href=\"#parcel\" aria-label=\"parcel permalink\" class=\"anchor\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" focusable=\"false\" height=\"16\" version=\"1.1\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\" width=\"16\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z\"></path></svg></a>Parcel</h2>\n<p><span\n      class=\"gatsby-resp-image-wrapper\"\n      style=\"position: relative; display: block; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto;  max-width: 657px;\"\n    >\n      <a\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-link\"\n    href=\"/static/6c505972f2ef2bb9301c1c3fbe5b2434/702f6/0.png\"\n    style=\"display: block\"\n    target=\"_blank\"\n    rel=\"noopener\"\n  >\n    <span\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-background-image\"\n    style=\"padding-bottom: 111.11111111111111%; position: relative; bottom: 0; left: 0; background-image: url('data:image/png;base64,'); background-size: cover; display: block;\"\n  ></span>\n  <img\n        class=\"gatsby-resp-image-image\"\n        alt=\"0\"\n        title=\"0\"\n        src=\"/static/6c505972f2ef2bb9301c1c3fbe5b2434/702f6/0.png\"\n        srcset=\"/static/6c505972f2ef2bb9301c1c3fbe5b2434/d5c4a/0.png 185w,\n/static/6c505972f2ef2bb9301c1c3fbe5b2434/04e89/0.png 370w,\n/static/6c505972f2ef2bb9301c1c3fbe5b2434/702f6/0.png 657w\"\n        sizes=\"(max-width: 657px) 100vw, 657px\"\n        loading=\"lazy\"\n      />\n  </a>\n    </span></p>\n<p>A new bundler called '<a href=\"https://github.com/parcel-bundler/parcel\">Parcel</a>' was\nreleased in December by <a href=\"https://twitter.com/devongovett\">Devon Govett</a>. Parcel\nis a web application bundler that values zero configuration. They reuse classic\nweb concepts, like using <code class=\"language-text\">index.html</code> as the entry point of the application,\nwhich makes it really easy and intuitive to get started with a new project. You\nonly have to create an <code class=\"language-text\">index.html</code> and run <code class=\"language-text\">parcel index.html</code> to get a working\napplication. They automatically detect what kind of web application you're\nrunning, and adapt the configuration to that if it's not specifically set.</p>\n<p>This is aligns perfectly with the values of CodeSandbox. There is almost no\nfriction to get started, and all the needed configuration is automatically\ndetected &#x26; installed. That's why I decided to <strong>finally</strong> build a Vanilla\ntemplate and use Parcel as our configuration behind it.</p>\n</section>\n<section>\n<h2 id=\"vanilla-template\"><a href=\"#vanilla-template\" aria-label=\"vanilla template permalink\" class=\"anchor\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" focusable=\"false\" height=\"16\" version=\"1.1\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\" width=\"16\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z\"></path></svg></a>Vanilla Template</h2>\n<p><span\n      class=\"gatsby-resp-image-wrapper\"\n      style=\"position: relative; display: block; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto;  max-width: 740px;\"\n    >\n      <a\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-link\"\n    href=\"/static/8a705d3619ac06fd012523c79b5aefc5/9d9ec/1.png\"\n    style=\"display: block\"\n    target=\"_blank\"\n    rel=\"noopener\"\n  >\n    <span\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-background-image\"\n    style=\"padding-bottom: 56.077116512992454%; position: relative; bottom: 0; left: 0; background-image: url('data:image/png;base64,'); background-size: cover; display: block;\"\n  ></span>\n  <img\n        class=\"gatsby-resp-image-image\"\n        alt=\"1\"\n        title=\"1\"\n        src=\"/static/8a705d3619ac06fd012523c79b5aefc5/bcf2d/1.png\"\n        srcset=\"/static/8a705d3619ac06fd012523c79b5aefc5/d5c4a/1.png 185w,\n/static/8a705d3619ac06fd012523c79b5aefc5/04e89/1.png 370w,\n/static/8a705d3619ac06fd012523c79b5aefc5/bcf2d/1.png 740w,\n/static/8a705d3619ac06fd012523c79b5aefc5/dbb75/1.png 1110w,\n/static/8a705d3619ac06fd012523c79b5aefc5/9d9ec/1.png 1193w\"\n        sizes=\"(max-width: 740px) 100vw, 740px\"\n        loading=\"lazy\"\n      />\n  </a>\n    </span></p>\n<p>We have a new sandbox called <code class=\"language-text\">vanilla</code>, unlike other sandboxes, this sandbox has\n<code class=\"language-text\">index.html</code> as its entry. From this <code class=\"language-text\">index.html</code> you can add <code class=\"language-text\">script</code> and\n<code class=\"language-text\">link</code> tags to other files and they will be added to the bundle. We support all\nloaders that Parcel supports, so we support:</p>\n<ul>\n<li><a href=\"https://github.com/babel/babel\">Babel</a></li>\n<li><a href=\"https://github.com/Microsoft/TypeScript\">TypeScript</a></li>\n<li><a href=\"https://github.com/sass/sass\">SCSS/Sass</a></li>\n<li><a href=\"https://github.com/less/less.js\">LESS</a></li>\n<li><a href=\"https://github.com/stylus/stylus\">Stylus</a></li>\n<li><a href=\"https://github.com/css-modules/css-modules\">CSS Modules</a></li>\n</ul>\n<p>We also recognize the difference between:</p>\n<div class=\"gatsby-highlight\">\n      <pre class=\"language-js\"><code class=\"language-js\"><span class=\"token keyword\">import</span> styles <span class=\"token keyword\">from</span> <span class=\"token string\">'./styles.css'</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">;</span></code></pre>\n      </div>\n<p>and</p>\n<div class=\"gatsby-highlight\">\n      <pre class=\"language-js\"><code class=\"language-js\"><span class=\"token keyword\">import</span> <span class=\"token string\">'./styles.css'</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">;</span></code></pre>\n      </div>\n<p>In the first code block we will generate CSS modules from the CSS file, and in\nthe second block we won't.</p>\n<p>You can try it out here:</p>\n<!-- https://vanilla.codesandbox.io -->\n<p><iframe src=\"https://codesandbox.io/embed/vanilla?fontsize=14&view=split\" style=\"width:100%; height:500px; border:0; border-radius: 4px; overflow:hidden;\"></iframe></p>\n<h4 id=\"configuration\"><a href=\"#configuration\" aria-label=\"configuration permalink\" class=\"anchor\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" focusable=\"false\" height=\"16\" version=\"1.1\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\" width=\"16\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z\"></path></svg></a>Configuration</h4>\n<p>Like Parcel, we automatically do configuration for you. We automatically detect\nif you're using <a href=\"https://github.com/facebook/react\">React</a> or\n<a href=\"https://github.com/preactjs/preact\">Preact</a> and will adjust our Babel\nconfiguration for it. We do support Babel/TypeScript configuration, so you can\nalso choose to do your own configuration by creating a <code class=\"language-text\">tsconfig.json</code> or a\n<code class=\"language-text\">.babelrc</code>.</p>\n<h4 id=\"github-zip-extraction--deployment-integration\"><a href=\"#github-zip-extraction--deployment-integration\" aria-label=\"github zip extraction  deployment integration permalink\" class=\"anchor\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" focusable=\"false\" height=\"16\" version=\"1.1\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\" width=\"16\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z\"></path></svg></a>GitHub, Zip Extraction &#x26; Deployment Integration</h4>\n<p>Like the other templates, you can create repos, make commits and PRs, download\nand deploy sandboxes using this template. Without leaving the browser.</p>\n</section>\n<section>\n<h2 id=\"beta-warning\"><a href=\"#beta-warning\" aria-label=\"beta warning permalink\" class=\"anchor\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" focusable=\"false\" height=\"16\" version=\"1.1\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\" width=\"16\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z\"></path></svg></a>Beta Warning</h2>\n<p>This is our first template that uses HTML as an entry point, so there can be\nbugs or unintended behaviour that still needs to be solved. Please\n<a href=\"https://github.com/codesandbox/codesandbox-client/issues/new/choose\">let us know in the repo</a>\nif you find any issues!</p>\n</section>\n<section>\n<h2 id=\"thanks\"><a href=\"#thanks\" aria-label=\"thanks permalink\" class=\"anchor\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" focusable=\"false\" height=\"16\" version=\"1.1\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\" width=\"16\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z\"></path></svg></a>Thanks</h2>\n<p>I want to thank <a href=\"https://twitter.com/devongovett\">Devon Govett</a> for building\nthis beautiful bundler, I was able to effortlessly build an application in it.\nGreat work!</p>\n<p>If you like what we're doing, consider becoming a\n<a href=\"https://github.com/codesandbox/codesandbox-client\">contributor</a> or a\n<a href=\"http://codesandbox.io/patron\">patron</a>! You can stay up to date with CodeSandbox\nnews either on <a href=\"https://twitter.com/CompuIves\">@CompuIves</a> or\n<a href=\"https://twitter.com/codesandbox\">@codesandbox</a>.</p>\n</section>"}},"pageContext":{"isCreatedByStatefulCreatePages":false,"id":"f4aa66e7-7a2c-5766-9d04-9391d6e0bbb3"}}}